data.enText: the edge of sth in the shape of a circle

data.chText: 他从杯口的上方看着他们。
data.enText: He looked at them over the rim of his glass.
The rims of her eyes were red with crying.
the metal edge of a wheel onto which the tyre is fixed
having a particular type of rim
red-rimmed eyes (= for example, from crying)
to form an edge around sth

tr: the top edge of a vessel or other container
a projection used for strength or for attaching to another object
the outer part of a wheel to which the tire is attached
(basketball) the hoop from which the net is suspended
example: the ball hit the rim and bounced off

tr: the shape of a raised edge of a more or less circular object

value.def: The rim of a container such as a cup or glass is the edge that goes all the way round the top.

example.ex: She looked at him over the rim of her glass.
example.tran: 她的目光越过玻璃杯的边沿看着他。

value.def: The rim of a circular object is its outside edge.

example.ex: ...a round mirror with white metal rim.
example.tran: 镶着白色金属边框的圆镜子

value.def: If there is a rim of dirt around a surface there is a dirty mark around it.

example.ex: There was already a rim of dark hairs and soap round the basin.
example.tran: 洗脸盆边上已经有一圈黑头发和肥皂沫。

value.def: In basketball, the rim is the metal ring that holds the net through which players have to try to throw the ball to score.
